name: FontAwesome
comment:
<link rel="stylesheet" href="https://use.fontawesome.com/releases/v5.1.1/css/all.css"/>
Learn more at [FontAwesome](https://fontawesome.com/).

    import FontAwesome as FA
      exposing ( stylesheet
               , Icon(Paw)
               , Weight(Solid)
               , paw
               )

    pawIcon1 : Html msg
    pawIcon1 = Html.i [] <| Paw Solid

    pawIcon2 : Html msg
    pawIcon2 = paw

    view : Model -> Html msg
    view model
      = div []
        [ stylesheet
        , pawIcon1
        , pawIcon2
        ]

aliases.type: { size : Maybe.Maybe FontAwesome.Size , fixedWidth : Bool , bordered : Bool , inverted : Bool , pull : Maybe.Maybe (FontAwesome.ShiftX ()) , animation : Maybe.Maybe FontAwesome.Animation }

aliases.name: Transform

values.name: i
values.comment:
import FontAwesome as FA exposing (..)

    myIconStyle : Style
    myIconStyle
      = { size       = Nothing
        , fixedWidth = False
        , bordered   = False
        , inverted   = False
        , pull       = Nothing
        , animation  = Nothing
        , transform  = Nothing
        }

    myFlaskIcon : Html msg
    myFlaskIcon 
      = FA.i [ FA.style myIconStyle ] (Flask Regular)
      
    i_ : (Weight -> Icon) -> Html msg
    i_ icon 
      = FA.i [ FA.style myIconStyle ] (icon Regular)
      
    myEasyFlaskIcon : Html msg
      = i_ Flask

values.name: layers
values.comment:
Compose multiple icons into a single icon!

    layers []
    [ LayerIcon    [ transform myTransform ] (Envelope Regular)
    , LayerCounter [                       ] TopRight "42"
    ]
values.type: List (Html.Attribute msg) -> List (FontAwesome.Layer msg) -> Html.Html msg

values.name: li
values.comment:
myList 
      = FA.li 
        [              ]  -- Html.li attributes
        [              ]  -- FA.i  attributes
        (Square Regular)  -- FA.i  body
        [ text "Howdy" ]  -- Html.li body
values.type: List (Html.Attribute msg) -> List (Html.Attribute msg) -> FontAwesome.Icon -> List (Html.Html msg) -> Html.Html msg

values.name: mask
values.comment:
Compose two icons, where one is subtracted from the other.

    mask []
    FacebookF         -- cutout icon (see-thru)
    (Circle Regular)  -- outer icon (opaque)
values.type: List (Html.Attribute msg) -> FontAwesome.Icon -> FontAwesome.Icon -> Html.Html msg

values.name: size
values.comment:
import FontAwesome as FA
      exposing ( i
               , Size(..)
               , Icon(..)
               , Weight(..)
               )

    myBigIcon : Html msg
    myBigIcon = i [ size Large ] <| Eye Solid

values.name: style
values.comment:
import FontAwesome as FA
      exposing ( i
               , style
               , Size(..)
               , ShiftX(..)
               , Animation(..)
               , Icon(..)
               , Weight(..)
               )

    coolSpinner : Html msg
    coolSpinner
      = i [ style 
            { size       = Just X10
            , fixedWidth = True
            , bordered   = False
            , inverted   = False
            , pull       = Just (Right ())
            , animation  = Pulse
            }
          ]
        <| Spinner Solid

values.name: stylesheet
values.comment:
Include FontAwesome 5.0.6 in your Elm project.

    import FontAwesome as FA
      exposing ( stylesheet
               , Icon(Meh)
               , Weight(Solid)
               )

    view : Model -> Html msg
    view model
      = div []
        [ stylesheet
        , FA.i [] <| Meh Solid
        ]

values.name: toClassName
values.comment:
FA.toClassName (PaintBrush Regular)
    -- "far fa-paint-brush"

    FA.toClassName (PaintBrush Solid)
    -- "fas fa-paint-brush"

    FA.toClassName (PaintBrush Light)
    -- "fal fa-paint-brush"

    FA.toClassName PiedPiper
    -- "fab fa-pied-piper"

values.name: transform
values.comment:
import FontAwesome as FA
      exposing ( i
               , transform
               , Scale(..)
               , ShiftX(..)
               , ShiftY(..)
               , Icon(Magic)
               , Weight(Solid)
               )

    wackyWand : Html msg
    wackyWand
      = i [ transform
            { scale  = Just <| Grow 17.1
            , shiftX = Just <| Left 25.5
            , shiftY = Just <| Down 12.9
            , rotate = Just <|      90.0
            }
          ]
        <| Magic Solid

values.name: ul
values.comment: Creates an icon list! Use this to make unordered lists with your favorite icons as bullets.
